<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Does this theme work with Elementor or page builders?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Yes, you can use Elementor or your page builder of choice with any of our themes. Blockify provides a Full Width page template which is perfect for creating full-width pages between the site header and footer. There is also a Blank page template which can be used to create complete pages, including header and footer, with your page builder.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Please note that blocks cannot be edited with page builders. Blocks can be customized with the WordPress block editor. Page builders can be used to replace parts of your site, however they can't be used to edit blocks.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How to change the site logo?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Head to the Site Editor and then navigate to the Header Template Part. From there, click on the existing logo and then replace it with a block of your choice. You can use an Image block, SVG, Site Logo or Site Title block as the site logo, the choice is yours. We prefer to use SVGs for logos because they scale perfectly at all screen sizes and also support variable colors which makes them ideal for use with dark mode and animations.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How do I add custom SVG images?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Custom SVG images can be added to your site in multiple ways. The first option is to use the core Image block, however this requires the use of the Safe SVG plugin since WordPress doesn't allow SVG uploads by default. There is also an SVG block variation provided with this theme which lets you simply paste SVG HTML code into an Image block. The third option is to use the Icon block variation. This displays an SVG icon which you can choose from a library of included icons, or upload your own.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
