<p>PHP 7.4 or higher is required however we recommend using a later version PHP 8.2 or above. All themes are tested with the latest version of WordPress.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default has-neutral-950-color has-text-color has-link-color has-20-font-size" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How can I display blog posts on the home page?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>This theme comes with multiple blog patterns that can be used to display posts on any page. Simply add a blog pattern to your home page template, or the page that is set as the Front Page. You can customize the Query Loop to suit your needs. Front page settings can be found from the WordPress admin dashboard under Settings → Reading.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|neutral-950"}}}},"textColor":"neutral-950","className":"is-style-default","fontSize":"20","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
